{"version":2,"width":100,"height":30,"timestamp":1778147350,"title":"diffnotes usage tour","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/zsh","TERM":"xterm-256color"}}
[0.000000,"o","\u001b[2J\u001b[H\u001b[1;36m# diffnotes usage tour\u001b[0m\r\n\r\nUse this tool when you want to review local git changes, leave line comments,\r\nand copy a structured prompt for an LLM coding agent.\r\n\r\nThis recording uses the diffnotes repository itself as the example repo.\r\n"]
[1.200000,"o","\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ git clone git@github.com:alexfedosov/diffnotes.git\u001b[0m\r\nCloning into 'diffnotes'...\r\n"]
[2.100000,"o","\u001b[1;32m$ cd diffnotes\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.800000,"o","\u001b[1;32m$ git status --short\u001b[0m\r\n M README.md\r\n M internal/clipboard/clipboard.go\r\n"]
[4.000000,"o","\r\nThere are unstaged changes. Open diffnotes at the repo root:\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ diffnotes --repo .\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[5.000000,"o","\u001b[2J\u001b[H diffnotes  repo:diffnotes  source:Unstaged changes  comments:0\r\n> SOURCES                 |    README.md  (modified)\r\n--------------------------|  @@ -65,7 +65,9 @@ Clipboard Support\r\n* Unstaged changes  2 files|   65    65   ## Clipboard Support\r\n  2898ae7 Prefer OSC52 cl>|   66    66\r\n  e114520 Make manual rel>|   67    67   Clipboard copy uses the native command available on the current platform:\r\n  f67015f Fix manual rele>|   68    68\r\n  895c0b2 Merge remote ma>|   69    69   - macOS: `pbcopy`\r\n  8e02cac Add CI and rele>|   70    70   - Linux Wayland: `wl-copy`\r\n                          |   71    71   - Linux X11: `xclip` or `xsel`\r\n                          |   72    72   - Windows: `clip`\r\n                          |         73 +\r\n                          |         74 + When running over SSH, `diffnotes` prefers OSC 52 clipboard sequences...\r\n\r\n loaded Unstaged changes |  tab focus  j/k move  enter open/comment  a/e edit  d delete  z fold-comments  c copy  r reload  q quit\r\n"]
[7.000000,"o","\u001b[2J\u001b[H\u001b[1;32mKeys: f j j j j j a\u001b[0m\r\n\r\nMove focus to the diff, move to the SSH clipboard line, then press `a`.\r\nThe comment editor appears inline under the selected source line.\r\n\r\n diffnotes  repo:diffnotes  source:Unstaged changes  comments:0\r\n  SOURCES                 |    README.md  (modified)\r\n--------------------------|  @@ -65,7 +65,9 @@ Clipboard Support\r\n* Unstaged changes  2 files|   69    69   - macOS: `pbcopy`\r\n                          |   70    70   - Linux Wayland: `wl-copy`\r\n                          |   71    71   - Linux X11: `xclip` or `xsel`\r\n                          |   72    72   - Windows: `clip`\r\n                          |         73 +\r\n                          | >       74 + When running over SSH, `diffnotes` prefers OSC 52 clipboard sequences...\r\n                          |       + add comment: Make sure this is explicit because native Linux clipboard\r\n                          |         commands would copy on the remote host, not the developer laptop.\r\n\r\n editing comment |  enter save  esc cancel\r\n"]
[10.000000,"o","\u001b[2J\u001b[H\u001b[1;32mPress Enter to save.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n diffnotes  repo:diffnotes  source:Unstaged changes  comments:1\r\n  SOURCES                 |    README.md  (modified)\r\n--------------------------|  @@ -65,7 +65,9 @@ Clipboard Support\r\n* Unstaged changes  2 files|   70    70   - Linux Wayland: `wl-copy`\r\n                          |   71    71   - Linux X11: `xclip` or `xsel`\r\n                          |   72    72   - Windows: `clip`\r\n                          |         73 +\r\n                          | >       74 + When running over SSH, `diffnotes` prefers OSC 52 clipboard sequences...\r\n                          |         comment: Make sure this is explicit because native Linux clipboard\r\n                          |            commands would copy on the remote host, not the developer laptop.\r\n\r\n saved comment for README.md:74 |  tab focus  j/k move  enter open/comment  a/e edit  d delete  z fold-comments  c copy  r reload  q quit\r\n"]
[13.000000,"o","\u001b[2J\u001b[H\u001b[1;32mAdd another comment in internal/clipboard/clipboard.go.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n diffnotes  repo:diffnotes  source:Unstaged changes  comments:2\r\n  SOURCES                 |    internal/clipboard/clipboard.go  (modified)\r\n--------------------------|  @@ -18,7 +18,14 @@ type candidate struct {\r\n* Unstaged changes  2 files|   18    18   }\r\n                          |   19    19\r\n                          |         20 + const clipboardModeEnv = \"DIFFNOTES_CLIPBOARD\"\r\n                          |         21 +\r\n                          | >       22 + func shouldPreferOSC52() bool {\r\n                          |         comment: Good default for SSH. Keep the explicit native override so people\r\n                          |            can still use remote clipboard tools when they really want them.\r\n                          |         23 +     switch clipboardMode() {\r\n\r\n saved comment for internal/clipboard/clipboard.go:22\r\n"]
[16.000000,"o","\u001b[2J\u001b[H\u001b[1;32mPress z for folded comment view.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\nOnly commented lines are shown, with three lines of context above each one,\r\nstill grouped by file.\r\n\r\n diffnotes  repo:diffnotes  source:Unstaged changes  comments:2  folded\r\n  SOURCES                 |    README.md  (modified)\r\n--------------------------|   71    71   - Linux X11: `xclip` or `xsel`\r\n* Unstaged changes  2 files|   72    72   - Windows: `clip`\r\n                          |         73 +\r\n                          | >       74 + When running over SSH, `diffnotes` prefers OSC 52 clipboard sequences...\r\n                          |         comment: Make sure this is explicit because native Linux clipboard\r\n                          |            commands would copy on the remote host, not the developer laptop.\r\n                          |\r\n                          |    internal/clipboard/clipboard.go  (modified)\r\n                          |   19    19\r\n                          |         20 + const clipboardModeEnv = \"DIFFNOTES_CLIPBOARD\"\r\n                          |         21 +\r\n                          | >       22 + func shouldPreferOSC52() bool {\r\n                          |         comment: Good default for SSH. Keep the explicit native override so people\r\n                          |            can still use remote clipboard tools when they really want them.\r\n\r\n showing comments with 3 lines of context |  z full diff  c copy\r\n"]
[20.000000,"o","\u001b[2J\u001b[H\u001b[1;32mPress c to copy all comments.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\nOn local macOS this uses `pbcopy`.\r\nOn local Linux this uses `wl-copy`, `xclip`, or `xsel`.\r\nOver SSH it prefers OSC 52, so the text lands in your local terminal clipboard.\r\n\r\n status: copied 2 comments using OSC 52 terminal clipboard\r\n"]
[23.000000,"o","\r\nThe clipboard text is structured for a coding agent:\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;37mReview comments for coding agent\u001b[0m\r\n\r\nSource: Unstaged changes (2 files)\r\n- README.md:74 [new]\r\n  Message: Make sure this is explicit because native Linux clipboard commands would copy on the remote host, not the developer laptop.\r\n  Code: When running over SSH, `diffnotes` prefers OSC 52 clipboard sequences...\r\n\r\n- internal/clipboard/clipboard.go:22 [new]\r\n  Message: Good default for SSH. Keep the explicit native override so people can still use remote clipboard tools when they really want them.\r\n  Code: func shouldPreferOSC52() bool {\r\n"]
[28.000000,"o","\r\n\u001b[1;36mDone.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\nTypical flow:\r\n  1. Run `diffnotes --repo .`\r\n  2. Pick `Unstaged changes`, `Staged changes`, `Untracked files`, or a commit.\r\n  3. Press `a` or `enter` on a changed line to leave an inline comment.\r\n  4. Press `z` to review only comments with context.\r\n  5. Press `c` to copy the agent-ready review text.\r\n"]
